description:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Red features a University Red leather upper with white leather overlays and Swooshes. A matching sole and woven tongue label adds the finishing touches to this retro design.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Red released in September of 2021 and retailed for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low Championship Red (2021)

description:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Grey features a grey mesh upper with layered suede overlays and white leather doubled Swooshes. On the side of the doubled sole, both sacai and Fragment branding is printed in black. From there, a doubled tongue with woven labels completes the design.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Grey released in August of 2021 and retailed for $170.
name: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Grey

description:
The Nike Dunk Mid Social Status Chocolate Milk fully embodies the staple cafeteria beverage. It arrives in a tonal brown velour and tumbled leather construction with pink semi-translucent Swooshes. From there, green Social Status and Nike branded tongues are reminiscent of milk crates.

The Nike Dunk Mid Social Status Chocolate Milk released in September of 2021 and retailed.
name: Nike Dunk Mid Social Status Free Lunch Chocolate Milk

description:
Taking cues from the Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss of Death, the Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze boasts an off-white translucent and suede upper with Deep Red and Orange Blaze snake-textured Swooshes. From there, a two-toned stacked sole and doubled tongue amplify sacai's unique design aesthetic.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze released in September of 2021 and retailed for $170.
name: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Net Orange Blaze

description:
The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog features a white leather upper with Grey Fog leather overlays and Swooshes. From there, a matching woven tongue label, heel tab, and sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog released in September of 2021 and retailed for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog

description:
From the school-spirited College Colors Program to the vibrant Nike CO.JP collection, Nike Dunks have seen many colorways since the design’s inception in 1985. But with each new colorway, the Dunk’s classic color-blocking has remained in some capacity. Nike put its timeless color-blocking to work with the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black.

The upper Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black is constructed of white leather with black leather overlays and Swooshes. Classic Nike Air branding is featured on the nylon tongue, nodding to traditional Dunk design elements. A white midsole and black outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black released in January of 2021 and retailed for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (2021)

description:
Boasting clashing camouflage patterns, the Nike Dunk Low Sail Multi-Camo is a statement piece. The design utilizes a white leather base to prominently display its multi-color camo overlays, which feature five different styles of camo. Green Swooshes and vibrant orange Nike embroidery on the heel tabs add the finishing touches.

The Nike Dunk Low Sail Multi-Camo released in August of 2021 and retailed for $110.
name: Nike Dunk Low SE Sail Multi-Camo

description:
The Nike Dunk Low Georgetown arrives with a smooth grey leather upper with Midnight Navy overlays and Swooshes. From there, matching woven Nike Air tongue tags, heel tabs, and Air soles complete the retro design.

The Nike Dunk Low Georgetown releases in October of 2021 and retails for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low Georgetown

description:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Blue Void combines the best of both sacai and Fragment's aesthetics. The mesh, leather, and suede construction of the LDWaffle represents sacai's experimental outlook, while the black and Blue Void palette is more reserved, similar to the utilitarian look that many of Fragment's collaborations have.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Blue Void released in August of 2021 and retailed for $170.
name: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Blue Void

description:
The Nike Dunk Low Undefeated 5 On It features a blue leather upper with snake print overlays, purple canvas quarter panels, and white suede Swooshes. From there, Undefeated logos on the heel and woven tongue label complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Undefeated 5 On It released in August of 2021 and retailed for $120.
name: Nike Dunk Low Undefeated 5 On It Dunk vs. AF1

description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Undefeated 5 On It features an assortment of textiles and sharp prints including faux snakeskin, Durabuck, suede, leather, and canvas. Similar to other releases in the Dunk vs. AF1 pack, Undefeated logos are prominent on the lateral heel and tongue label.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Undefeated 5 On It released in August of 2021 and retailed for $120.
name: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Undefeated 5 On It Dunk vs. AF1
Nike x Drake NOCTA Golf Crewneck Top Green
Nike Dunk High Championship Navy
Nike x Drake NOCTA Golf Mock Neck Top Black

description:
Nike and Dutch artist and sneaker collab veteran Parra teamed up for an Olympic inspired Nike SB Dunk Low with the Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art highlights Parra's surreal take on pop art. Off-white leather on the upper creates a blank canvas so that overlays smothered in vibrant, retro Parra patterns rise to prominence. Additional details like the embroidered mini-Swoosh on the toe box and gum outsole offer nostalgic appeal.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art released in July of 2021 and retailed for $110.
name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Parra Abstract Art (2021)

description:
The Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash features a dark grey leather upper with blotty Chile Red leather overlays and a monotone Swoosh. From there, a yellowed midsole and Nike woven tongue tag add a vintage touch.

The Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash released in August of 2021 and retailed for $130.
name: Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash

description:
The Nike Blazer Low sacai British Tan features a British Tan suede and leather upper with bold red accents. Much like previous designs in the Nike x sacai catalog, doubled Swooshes, overlays, tongues, and soles honor sacai's reconstructive design aesthetic.

The Nike Blazer Low sacai British Tan released in August of 2021 and retailed for $120.
name: Nike Blazer Low sacai British Tan

description:
The Nike Dunk High Game Royal pays homage to the original 1985 University of Kentucky colorway of the Nike Dunk. It features a white leather upper with Game Royal overlays and Swooshes. A matching sole and woven tongue label add the finishing touches.

The Nike Dunk High Game Royal released in June of 2021 and retailed for $110.
name: Nike Dunk High Game Royal

description: The black Drake x Nike Certified Lover Boy Rose T-shirt dropped on October 26th, 2020, shortly after the artist's birthday as he announced his new album. Drake's new album, "Certified Lover Boy" was announced that day to be releasing in January 2021 via a video posted to his Instagram. This white t-shirt was released alongside eleven other items and features a Nike Swoosh above the letters CLB on the front. The back of the t-shirt features the name of the album in a gold print with two roses laid over it and Drake branding across the bottom of the shirt. A white colorway of this Drake x Nike t-shirt was also released. The Drake x Nike Certified Lover Boy Rose T-shirt in black dropped at a retail price of $35 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Rose T-Shirt Black

description: This white Nike x Drake t-shirt dropped as a part of the artist's collaborative "Certified Lover Boy" album merch, which released the day that the album was announced. The announcement and drop came as a shock to some, following the artist's 34th birthday by just two days. The drop came out of nowhere but had been rumored for months as the collection had been leaked by Drake himself on his IG story earlier in 2020. The white Nike x Drake Certified Lover boy Rose T-shirt features a black Nike Swoosh above gold lettering that spells out CLB on the front. On the back of the shirt, two roses cover the words "Certified Lover Boy" which is written in the same gold color and font as the lettering on the front. This white Nike x Drake t-shirt dropped on October 26th, 2020, for $35 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Rose T-Shirt White

description: The white version of the Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Cherub T-shirt mimics the black version, delivering the inverse in color. This t-shirt features Drake "Certified Lover Boy" branding on the back and Nike branding on the front above a graphic of a masked cherub drawing it's bow and aiming its shot. In full, the collection included twelve items, but four of those items, including the jackets from the capsule, were friends and family exclusives. This white Nike x Drake t-shirt was dropped two days after Drake's birthday on October 26th, 2020, at a retail price of $35 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Cherub T-Shirt White

description: Drake and Nike released a collaborative merchandise capsule in late October, 2020, for the artist's new album, "Certified Lover Boy." Though the album would not drop until several months after the merch capsule was dropped, Drake set the stage for the album's release with his Nike collaboration. The Drake Certified Lover Boy capsule included 12 pieces, of which four were friends and family only. The Certified Lover Boy Hat design was leaked months before it's release on Drake's Instagram Story and features a single Nike swoosh and a lipstick kiss mark on the brim. The Drake Nike Certified Lover Boy Hat released on October 26th, 2020, and retailed for the price of $28 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Hat White

description:
In 2021, Nike brought back the classic 2010 Nike LeBron 8 South Beach. The upper consists of a mix of Filament Green leather and carbon fiber. From there, hits of Pink Flash appear on the laces and inner lining. Lastly, a lion head is embossed on the tongue to symbolize LeBron’s status as king of the court.

The Nike LeBron 8 South Beach (2021) releases July of 2021 for $200.
name: Nike LeBron 8 South Beach (2021)

description:
The Nike Dunk High Panda brings a neutral color tone to the popular Dunk High silhouette.

Smooth black and white full-grain leather make up the entire upper of the Nike Dunk High Panda (2021). A black outsole and white midsole continue the Panda motif while a University Red Nike Air Swoosh logo is embroidered on the tongue tag to add a pop of color.

The Nike Dunk High Panda (2021) released in July of 2021 for $110.
name: Nike Dunk High Panda (2021)

description:
Another one of the first Nike Dunk colorways from the 1985 “Be True To Your School” returned in 2020, this time in the form of the Nike Dunk High Varsity Maize. The Varsity Maize colorway pays homage to the University of Iowa, one of the first universities to partner with Nike. Also known as the “Golden Rod”, the Nike Dunk High Iowa has inspired a few renowned Dunks, most notably the 2005 Nike SB Dunk High Golden Rod and the Wu-Tang Dunk High.

The Nike Dunk High Varsity Maize arrives in its original form, featuring a black and yellow leather upper with traditional Dunk color blocking. A woven black and yellow Nike Swoosh tongue tag, white midsole, and Varsity Maize outsole finalize this latest Dunk re-issue.

The Nike Dunk High Varsity Maize released in December of 2020 and retailed for $120.
name: Nike Dunk High Varsity Maize

description: Drake's collaborative merch capsule with Nike for his new album, "Certified Lover Boy," was dropped ahead of the album's release in October of 2020. The collection's black Cherub t-shirt features a graphic of a masked cherup with its bow drawn underneath a Nike Swoosh logo on the front and features the name of Drake's new album on the back of the t-shirt. The collection itself dropped on October 26th, 2020, two days after Drake's birthday and included twelve items, four of which were for friends and family only. The Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Cherub T-shirt in black was released at a retail price of $35 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Cherub T-Shirt Black
Nike x Drake NOCTA Golf Mock Neck Top White
Nike Dunk SB High RX-0 Unicorn Gundam

description:
Travis Scott and Nike add a new design to their growing Air Force arsenal with the Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack, now available on StockX. After a year of sneaker world dominance, Nike is adding a twist to their latest collaborative AF 1 with Cactus Jack. This new design features a never before seen detachable lace cover that encloses with a heavy brass zipper.

This Travis AF-1 features a patchwork upper comprised of camouflage, corduroy, duck canvas, flannel, leather, suede and wool. Unmistakable Cactus Jack insignias are placed throughout the silhouette. A sail midsole and gum rubber outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in November of 2019 and retailed for $160.
name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack

description:
Nike brought back an 80s basketball classic with the Nike Dunk High Michigan. The Maize and blue colorway was one of the seven original Dunk High colorways that debuted in 1985 as part of Nike’s College Colors Program, a campaign that brought school-spirited colorways to footwear in college basketball.

The Nike Dunk High Michigan stays true to its original form. As a reference to the University of Michigan Wolverines, Maize and navy blue leather make up the upper. A white midsole, navy outsole, and Nike branding on the tongue sum up this design in a traditional fashion.

The Nike Dunk High Michigan released in September of 2020 and retailed for $120.
name: Nike Dunk High Michigan (2020)

description:
The Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Racer Blue Pink Glow features a marled Racer Blue and Pink Glow loose knit upper atop a thick ZoomX foam footbed with spiked rubber soles. In the sole, a stacked Zoom Air unit adds extra cushion for high impact areas.

The Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Racer Blue Pink Glow released in July of 2021 and retailed for $260.
name: Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Racer Blue Pink Glow

description:
The Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Black Scream Green provides a deconstructed, hand-crafted feel that is in line with most of Abloh’s aesthetic. Appearing in a Black and Scream Green color scheme, the model features a loose knit upper atop a thick ZoomX foam footbed with spiked rubber soles. Details like imperfectly printed Swooshes accentuate its prototype appeal.

The Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Black Scream Green released in July of 2021 and retailed for $260.
name: Nike Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Off-White Black Scream Green
Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Hoodie Navy

description:
Travis Scott teamed up with Nike SB to release his first official skate shoe, the Nike SB Dunk Low Travis Scott (Regular Box), now available on StockX. This design follows a similar design aesthetic as seen on the Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack, featuring an array of materials and prints. Unlike previous Travis Scott releases, these were not available on SNKRS and only available at select Nike SB stockists.

This Nike SB Dunk Low is composed of suede upper with paisley canvas and plaid flannel overlays. As the paisley overlays wear off, an elephant print is revealed. Embroidered text around the collar, rope laces, and La Flame’s Cactus Jack logo on the puffy tongues completes this design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $150.
name: Nike SB Dunk Low Travis Scott (Regular Box)

description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Kentucky colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with varsity royal leather overlays. A white midsole, royal outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low SP Kentucky (2020)

description: The Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Socks dropped alongside eleven other items on October 26th, 2020, as the artist dropped a full merch capsule in coincidence with an announcement for his new album. Featuring Nike Air branded hearts on the sides, the Dri-Fit Drake designed socks have been likened to a similar and popular pair of socks created by Comme des Garçons. The socks dropped only in a white colorway but matches well with the Nike x Drake hat dropped in the same capsule. The Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Socks were released at a retail price of $18 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Socks White
Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Socks Black

description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Syracuse colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with orange blaze leather overlays. A white midsole, orange outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue complete the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.
name: Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020)

description: Drake's "Certified Lover Boy" merchandise capsule was dropped without announcement just two days after his 34th birthday. The release included twelve different merch items from collaborative Nike hats to t-shirt to socks and hoodies. The black Drake x Nike Certified Lover Boy Hoodie features a yellow Swoosh logo over a graphic of the letters CLB and two roses. This Drake Merch hoodie was released alongside a grey version that also features Nike branding. This black Drake x Nike Hoodie was released on the artist's webstore for a retail price of $75 USD on October 26th, 2020.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Hoodie Black

description: This grey Drake x Nike Hoodie released on October 26th, 2020, only two days after Drake turned 34 years old. The drop came on the same day that his new album, "Certified Lover Boy" was announced via a short video that shows Drake reflecting on his past albums. The grey hoodie from Drake's "Certified Lover Boy" album merch capsule features the letters CLB beneath two roses under a yellow Nike Swoosh logo. This hoodie released alongside eleven other Drake x Nike Certified Lover Boy pieces and retailed at a price of $75 USD.
name: Nike x Drake Certified Lover Boy Hoodie Grey
